                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-732" type="surname" value="PUMMELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-732" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PUMMELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my mother. On the Saturday in question, I saw the prisoner in Twister's-alley, carrying a kettle before him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350202-name-733" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-733" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-733" type="surname" value="KERSHAW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350202-name-733" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN KERSHAW</persName>
                  </hi>. I was on duty in Whitecross-street—a boy came to me and said a man had stolen a kettle—I found the prisoner on Monday night last at the Refuge for the Destitute—I apprehended his mother on the Saturday—she had been to sell the kettle in Plough-yard.</p>
